qas.question: What did Nasser completely eliminate from Egypt?
What did Nasser work to put into place in Egypt?
How were working conditions and employment at the end of Nasser's presidency?
What had drained resources from Nasser's social programs?

context: Nasser made Egypt fully independent of <a0_0>British influence<a0_0/>, and the country became a major power in the developing world under his leadership. One of Nasser's main domestic efforts was to establish <a1_0>social justice<a1_0/>, which he deemed a prerequisite to liberal democracy. During his presidency, ordinary citizens enjoyed unprecedented access to housing, education, jobs, health services and nourishment, as well as other forms of social welfare, while feudalistic influence waned. By the end of his presidency, employment and working conditions <a2_0>improved considerably<a2_0/>, although poverty was still high in the country and substantial resources allocated for social welfare had been diverted to the <a3_0>war effort<a3_0/>.
